I’ve narrowed the next cut to a real runtime blocker instead of broad cleanup: `SyncNode` needs per-session key resolution for account-scoped app usage. I’m patching that in `happy-sync`, wiring the app store to provide the resolver, and adding integration coverage before I touch higher-level UI behavior.
Plan update
Implementing the missing account-scoped SyncNode key resolution path, then verifying it with tests before considering any broader cleanup.
  → Add per-session key resolution support to happy-sync SyncNode and expose the new types
  • Wire AppSyncStore/app encryption to provide session key resolution for account-scoped app usage
  • Add or update tests covering encrypted session hydration/message decryption with distinct session keys
  • Run targeted happy-sync and app-adjacent tests to verify the refactor
codex
