codex
Implemented a core missing piece from the refactor plan: account-scoped `SyncNode` can now resolve per-session data keys instead of assuming one key fits every session. The main changes are in [sync-node.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-sync/src/sync-node.ts), [sync-node.integration.test.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-sync/src/sync-node.integration.test.ts), [protocol.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-sync/src/protocol.ts), [syncNodeStore.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-app/sources/sync/syncNodeStore.ts), [encryption.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-app/sources/sync/encryption/encryption.ts), and [sync.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-app/sources/sync/sync.ts). I also added typed user-message `meta` support in [protocol.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-sync/src/protocol.ts) with coverage in [protocol.test.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-sync/src/protocol.test.ts).

Verified:
```sh
yarn workspace @slopus/happy-sync test:unit
yarn workspace @slopus/happy-sync test:integration
yarn workspace @slopus/happy-sync build
yarn workspace happy-app typecheck
yarn workspace happy-coder typecheck
```

This does not finish the entire spec. I did not complete the remaining Level 2/3 flow work or remove every legacy path in CLI/app yet.
